Ad Text:
12 + 12 month contract - 37.5 hours pw 
QLD, WA, ACT, VIC, NSW, NT, SA or TAS
Digital Transformation Program

Our client, a Commonwealth Government organisation whose focus is to provide support to Australian's living with disability, require the services of a Technical Business Analyst for a 12+12 month contract.

Duties of the Technical Business Analyst

Assist in the delivery of diverse & varied projects, centred around a large-scale digital transformation;
Ensure that requirements are captured, supporting the team to document solutions, processes & technical details;
Synthesise business & technical requirements/concepts & present them in simple terms;
Work with both traditional & Agile delivery practices including backlog creation / refinement & associated requirements gathering, data discovery & analysis;
Facilitate workshops & perform business analysis activities including business process modelling, business & solution requirements lifecycle management & data modelling. 

Skills and Experience Required 

At least 5 years' experience working in a similar role performing business analysis activities including workshop facilitation;
Proven experience, of at least 3 years, in a role relating to cloud platforms (preferably Amazon Web Services & Microsoft Azure) including delivery of new services;
Proven experience, of at least 3 years in a role supporting Staff-facing internal systems such as recruitment portals, Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) systems, Learning systems, performance management systems & other similar enabling systems;
Demonstrated experience in effectively communicating with technical SME's to define and obtain an understanding of business needs, technical constraints, & technical concepts.  Presenting them in simple terms;
Experience in working with diverse project, in-house development, & vendor teams to deploy complex, integrated technologies & effect business change (desired);
Demonstrated experience and flexibility to adapt to agile and waterfall processes to deliver projects (desired).

How to Apply 
For a copy of the full job description, including the application instructions, please get in touch with Ben at Recruitment Hive by clicking the Quick Apply button. Alternatively you can reach Ben on (02) 6299 1006 to discuss further. 

Please note that applications close on Friday the 15th of May 2026 at 11am. Recruitment Hive welcome late applications to be considered for future opportunities. 

